{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:45.773450+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_049b6417-b94f-4ff9-9eb4-efb1f21869c4"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_90c6a9c4-5c9b-4866-954e-9aff7eaae637"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "3c367a5d-57d6-4d72-a59a-46e4a72570c6", "tool_call_id": "call_00_D3m8MR8Mu1BXA3qkahr77117", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:54.575836+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 757, "prompt_tokens": 4097, "total_tokens": 4854, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 386, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 3072}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 3072, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 1025}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "40727c80-4998-4e1c-90be-f579ea8bfb4c", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e7-00ce-79c1-a36e-9174aefc4896-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the report, @BruceKZ — this is a real bug.\n\nThe script's comment claims \"Order: filename glob, lexicographic\" and \"Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE\", but shell glob expansion order depends on `LC_COLLATE` and the filesystem's directory entry ordering. On macOS with APFS (case-insensitive) and `en_US.UTF-8`, the glob can return entries in an unexpected order, causing `003_add_session_index.sql` to run before `002_create_sessions.sql`.\n\nThe workaround you suggested is reasonable, though I'd recommend using a more robust pattern to avoid potential issues with filenames containing spaces or special characters:\n\n```bash\nwhile IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone < <(find migrations/ -maxdepth 1 -name '*.sql' -print0 | sort -z)\n```\n\nOr, for simplicity (if filenames are guaranteed safe):\n\n```bash\nfor f in $(ls migrations/*.sql | sort); do\n```\n\nHappy to accept a PR with the sorted-explicit loop approach."}, "id": "call_00_HDsmxBGkg5SN7Q9blC4C1771", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4097, "output_tokens": 757, "total_tokens": 4854, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 3072}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 386}}}}]}}}
